# Rudy Pi MCP Usage

When user asks about Rudy Pi, cortex service, CAN bus, Pi logs, Pi health, deploy/update status, runtime settings, inventory, audit logs, or systemd state on the Pi:

- Prefer `pi-cortex` MCP tools before shell or manual SSH.
- Use MCP for read-only checks when available: status, logs, CAN status, inventory, audit, settings.
- Use MCP mutating tools only for explicit user requests: restart cortex, force update, CAN bounce.
- Do not run arbitrary remote shell for Pi tasks unless MCP lacks needed surface or user explicitly asks.
- If MCP fails, report failure and fallback path clearly.
